original_title: Manhattan: Amsterdam Avenue - N.E. corner of Cathedral Parkway
text:
Amsterdam Avenue, at the N. E. corner of Cathedral Parkway (W. 110th Street) showing constructional details of the Protestant Episcopal Cathedral of St. John, the cornerstone of which was laid on St. John's Day, December 17, 1892 by Bishop Potter. The plans are by Heins and La Farge. This site was formerly occupied by the Leake and Watts Orphan Asylum.

About 1910

Ewing Galloway
